recital.p:
Following an application from Ecopharma BVBA, submitted pursuant to Article 13(5) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, the Authority was required to deliver an opinion on a health claim related to Fabenol® Max, a standardised aqueous extract from Phaseolus vulgaris L., and the reduction of the absorption of carbohydrates (Question No EFSA-Q-2015-00123

EFSA Journal 2016;14(2):4401.
                  ). The claim proposed by the applicant was worded as follows: 'Fabenol® Max reduces the absorption of carbohydrates'.

Following an application from DSM Nutritional Products, submitted pursuant to Article 13(5) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, the Authority was required to deliver an opinion on a health claim related to docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) and improvement of memory function (Question No EFSA-Q-2015-00456

EFSA Journal 2016;14(5):4455.
                  ). The claim proposed by the applicant was worded as follows: 'DHA contributes to improved memory function'.

Following an application from Tate & Lyle PLC, submitted pursuant to Article 13(5) of Regulation (EC) No 1924/2006, the Authority was required to deliver an opinion on a health claim related to polydextrose and normal defecation (Question No EFSA-Q-2015-00550

EFSA Journal 2016;14(5):4480.
                  ). The claim proposed by the applicant was worded as follows: 'Polydextrose contributes to an improved bowel function by increasing stool bulk'.
